Endogyne (
Figs 8B, D
, 
9E
, F–I, 10B, E, H, I, M, N): dorsal lobe of the anterior “receptacle” (
Dl
) S-shaped, cylindrical, with slightly thinner tip, lacking pillar-shaped glands; ventral lobe (
Vl
) of the anterior “receptacle” hexagonal, longer than wide, evenly covered with pillar-shaped glands (
Pi
); posterior “receptacle” (
Pr
) sac like, covered with numerous gland plates (
Pg
), each carrying from 2 to 8 conical glands standing in own compartments (
Fig. 10H
).
